main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified objects over Warner, New Hampshire in August 1963.
interesting points: Objects observed for 2-3 seconds described as clear-shaped with lights at each end,Initial observations noted a meteor shower, A large bright object estimated to be 25-30 feet in diameter was seen moving silently, Sightings were confirmed by two separate witnesses, One object reported to maneuver erratically at an estimated height of 3000 feet.
sighted object: Unidentified flying objects observed at night
